WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:07.000
Gasterly Ghosts by Gina D. B. Clemmel

00:31.000 --> 00:38.000
Chapter 1 What is a Ghost?

00:38.000 --> 00:50.000
Centuries ago, people talked about ghosts, spirits and spooks, and they still talk about them today.

00:50.000 --> 00:55.000
But no one knows exactly what a ghost is.

00:55.000 --> 01:05.000
Certain scientists and psychic experts study ghosts and haunted places.

01:05.000 --> 01:13.000
They try to understand supernatural events of the past and present.

01:13.000 --> 01:20.000
Psychic experts use complex machines to discover ghosts.

01:21.000 --> 01:26.000
Others try to photograph ghosts.

01:26.000 --> 01:34.000
Sometimes ghosts appear in photographs and no one can explain why.

01:34.000 --> 01:41.000
Today, several important universities have a parapsychology department.

01:41.000 --> 01:52.000
In these departments, experts study the supernatural and try to find an answer to old questions.

01:52.000 --> 01:56.000
So, what is a ghost?

01:56.000 --> 02:03.000
The most common explanation is this, ghosts are spirits of the dead.

02:03.000 --> 02:08.000
Their death was a tragic or terrible one.

02:08.000 --> 02:12.000
They haunt the place where they died.

02:12.000 --> 02:21.000
It can be a house, a castle, a theatre, a forest, a road or a ship.

02:21.000 --> 02:26.000
They cannot rest in peace.

02:26.000 --> 02:29.000
Do ghosts really exist?

02:29.000 --> 02:32.000
What do you think?

02:32.000 --> 02:38.000
Read this book carefully and become a ghost investigator.

02:38.000 --> 02:52.000
Fill in the phantom file with your opinion after each case and then decide.

02:52.000 --> 02:58.000
Chapter 2 The Horror of Barkley Square

02:58.000 --> 03:02.000
There are many ghosts in the city of London.

03:02.000 --> 03:09.000
There are haunted houses, theatres, streets and pubs.

03:09.000 --> 03:15.000
One of the most evil ghosts is the one at Barkley Square.

03:15.000 --> 03:24.000
Between 1870 and 1900, no one wanted to live at 50 Barkley Square.

03:24.000 --> 03:30.000
There were footsteps at night and macabre appearances.

03:30.000 --> 03:37.000
One particular room in the house was especially dangerous.

03:37.000 --> 03:47.000
In 1870, a brave young man decided to sleep in the haunted room for one night.

03:47.000 --> 03:51.000
Ghosts don't scare me, he said.

03:51.000 --> 03:55.000
The next morning, he was dead.

03:55.000 --> 04:00.000
His body was in the middle of the evil room.

04:00.000 --> 04:06.000
A year later, a young girl slept in the haunted room.

04:06.000 --> 04:13.000
That night, she saw or heard something horrible.

04:13.000 --> 04:17.000
The next morning, she was mad.

04:17.000 --> 04:25.000
She could not speak about her horrifying experience to anyone.

04:25.000 --> 04:29.000
Lord Littleton was an English lord.

04:29.000 --> 04:32.000
I don't believe in ghosts.

04:32.000 --> 04:34.000
He told his friends.

04:34.000 --> 04:39.000
I will sleep in that house and nothing will happen to me.

04:39.000 --> 04:49.000
During the night, the people in the next house heard a gunshot.

04:49.000 --> 04:55.000
The next morning, Lord Littleton was terrified and told them.

04:55.000 --> 04:59.000
Something came into the room from that corner.

04:59.000 --> 05:03.000
It was slimy and had an evil smell.

05:03.000 --> 05:07.000
I fired my gun at it and the ghost disappeared.

05:07.000 --> 05:09.000
It was horrible.

05:09.000 --> 05:12.000
I cannot describe it.

05:12.000 --> 05:17.000
That house is haunted by a ghastly spirit.

05:17.000 --> 05:23.000
A year later, a maid was cleaning the haunted room.

05:23.000 --> 05:27.000
She did not know about the evil ghost.

05:27.000 --> 05:33.000
At midnight, horrible cries.

05:33.000 --> 05:36.000
Came from the haunted room.

05:36.000 --> 05:38.000
Aah!

05:38.000 --> 05:43.000
The people in the house ran upstairs.

05:43.000 --> 05:49.000
They found the poor maid on the floor in convulsions.

05:49.000 --> 05:55.000
Her terrified eyes stared at a corner of the room.

05:55.000 --> 06:01.000
It was the same corner Lord Littleton indicated.

06:01.000 --> 06:04.000
The maid refused to speak.

06:04.000 --> 06:07.000
Her only words were...

06:07.000 --> 06:14.000
What I saw was too horrible to describe.

06:14.000 --> 06:20.000
The next morning, she died at St George's Hospital.

06:20.000 --> 06:28.000
The story of the two sailors is perhaps the most famous of all.

06:28.000 --> 06:34.000
In 1875, two sailors arrived in London.

06:34.000 --> 06:38.000
They wanted to work on a ship.

06:38.000 --> 06:43.000
They had no money and nowhere to sleep.

06:43.000 --> 06:48.000
They walked around London and came to Barclay Square.

06:48.000 --> 06:50.000
Look!

06:50.000 --> 06:52.000
Said the younger sailor.

06:52.000 --> 06:56.000
There's an empty house. We can sleep there.

06:56.000 --> 07:00.000
The sailors entered the dark empty house.

07:00.000 --> 07:03.000
They went up the stairs.

07:03.000 --> 07:06.000
The older sailor said...

07:06.000 --> 07:11.000
This house is cold and dark. I don't like it.

07:11.000 --> 07:13.000
It scares me.

07:13.000 --> 07:15.000
Don't be silly.

07:15.000 --> 07:17.000
Said the younger sailor.

07:17.000 --> 07:21.000
We have nowhere to sleep. Let's stay here.

07:21.000 --> 07:24.000
They slept in the haunted bedroom.

07:24.000 --> 07:29.000
In the middle of the night, they both woke up.

07:29.000 --> 07:30.000
Listen.

07:30.000 --> 07:32.000
Said the younger one.

07:32.000 --> 07:35.000
There's someone downstairs.

07:35.000 --> 07:37.000
Can you hear the noise?

07:37.000 --> 07:38.000
Yes.

07:38.000 --> 07:40.000
Said the other.

07:40.000 --> 07:42.000
I can hear footsteps.

07:42.000 --> 07:44.000
Oh no.

07:44.000 --> 07:48.000
The footsteps are coming upstairs.

07:48.000 --> 07:53.000
At that moment, the door opened slowly.

07:53.000 --> 07:57.000
A big dark figure came in.

07:57.000 --> 08:01.000
The older sailor was terrified.

08:01.000 --> 08:04.000
He could not move.

08:04.000 --> 08:10.000
He just sat and looked at the horrible thing.

08:10.000 --> 08:14.000
The younger sailor ran out of the room,

08:14.000 --> 08:18.000
down the stairs and out of the house.

08:18.000 --> 08:22.000
In the street, he found a policeman.

08:22.000 --> 08:28.000
They returned to the house, but the sailor was too frightened to enter.

08:28.000 --> 08:33.000
The policeman went upstairs alone.

08:33.000 --> 08:35.000
Is anyone here?

08:35.000 --> 08:37.000
He cried.

08:37.000 --> 08:43.000
There was no answer, and he found no one.

08:43.000 --> 08:48.000
There was an evil smell on the stairs.

08:48.000 --> 08:54.000
He looked everywhere, but he couldn't find the older sailor.

08:54.000 --> 08:58.000
Then he looked out of the window.

08:58.000 --> 09:03.000
The older sailor was lying in the garden.

09:03.000 --> 09:06.000
He was dead.

09:06.000 --> 09:10.000
Did something push him out of the window?

09:10.000 --> 09:15.000
Or did he jump out of the window in terror?

09:15.000 --> 09:23.000
We will never know.

09:23.000 --> 09:29.000
Listening exercise, Chapter 2.

09:29.000 --> 09:34.000
Listen to the conversation between the two sailors.

09:34.000 --> 09:43.000
For each question, choose the correct answer, A, B or C.

09:43.000 --> 09:46.000
What a rainy evening.

09:46.000 --> 09:50.000
I'm wet, and I'm tired of walking.

09:50.000 --> 09:54.000
You're right. I'm cold and very hungry.

09:54.000 --> 10:03.000
I'm very hungry, too. It's half past six. Look, there's a small bakery near the church.

10:03.000 --> 10:07.000
Yes. Let's go and see.

10:07.000 --> 10:12.000
I want to buy that big apple pie in the window.

10:12.000 --> 10:15.000
And I want some chocolate biscuits.

10:15.000 --> 10:21.000
Then we can go to the yellow duck tavern and have a hot cup of tea.

10:21.000 --> 10:27.000
What a good idea. It's always warm at the yellow duck tavern.

10:27.000 --> 10:30.000
Then we must find a place to sleep.

10:30.000 --> 10:41.000
Yes. But let's go to the barkly bakery first. I'm hungry.

10:41.000 --> 10:43.000
Chapter 3.

10:43.000 --> 10:48.000
Glam's Castle and its Ghosts.

10:48.000 --> 10:55.000
Scotland is famous for its haunted castles and its ghosts.

10:55.000 --> 11:02.000
Glam's Castle has a long history of violent murders and ghosts.

11:02.000 --> 11:12.000
It is a big castle with more than 100 rooms and many secret hiding places.

11:12.000 --> 11:18.000
The castle also hides terrible secrets.

11:18.000 --> 11:24.000
During the Middle Ages, there was a battle near the castle.

11:24.000 --> 11:29.000
After the battle, some men came to the castle.

11:29.000 --> 11:33.000
They were afraid and in danger.

11:33.000 --> 11:39.000
Excuse us, sir. We are in danger. The enemy is following us.

11:39.000 --> 11:42.000
Can we state your castle for a few days?

11:42.000 --> 11:44.000
They said.

11:44.000 --> 11:49.000
The Earl of Glam's smiled and said...

11:49.000 --> 11:54.000
Follow me. You can hide in a secret room.

11:54.000 --> 11:58.000
The men were happy and said...

11:58.000 --> 12:02.000
Thank you, sir. You are very kind.

12:02.000 --> 12:09.000
The Earl of Glam's looked at the men but did not answer.

12:09.000 --> 12:12.000
He took them to a secret room.

12:12.000 --> 12:16.000
Enter and don't make any noise.

12:16.000 --> 12:18.000
He said.

12:18.000 --> 12:21.000
The men entered.

12:21.000 --> 12:26.000
The Earl locked the door...

12:26.000 --> 12:30.000
and put the key in his pocket.

12:30.000 --> 12:35.000
He never opened that door again.

12:35.000 --> 12:43.000
Many years later, Lord Strathmore opened that door and fainted.

12:43.000 --> 12:48.000
He found a room full of skeletons.

12:48.000 --> 12:54.000
Visitors to the castle often hear strange noises in that room.

12:54.000 --> 13:00.000
They hear knocks at the door.

13:00.000 --> 13:05.000
Perhaps the ghosts of the men want to get out.

13:05.000 --> 13:11.000
The grey lady is another ghost of Glam's castle.

13:11.000 --> 13:19.000
Lady Janet Glam's lived during the reign of King James V of Scotland.

13:19.000 --> 13:25.000
King James was a cruel man and did not like Janet.

13:25.000 --> 13:31.000
Lady Janet Glam's is a witch. She tried to poison me.

13:31.000 --> 13:35.000
He said to his court.

13:35.000 --> 13:39.000
No. That is not true.

13:39.000 --> 13:48.000
Cried Lady Janet. I am not a witch. I am innocent.

13:48.000 --> 13:54.000
The king sent poor Lady Janet to prison for many years.

13:54.000 --> 13:58.000
And she was very unhappy.

13:58.000 --> 14:05.000
Then, in 1537, the king's men burned her.

14:05.000 --> 14:11.000
Her ghost haunts the clock tower of Glam's castle.

14:11.000 --> 14:15.000
People say her ghost is transparent.

14:15.000 --> 14:23.000
And there is a strange red light around her head.

14:23.000 --> 14:30.000
At the beginning of the 1800s, the Earl of Strathmore had a son.

14:30.000 --> 14:33.000
The baby was deformed.

14:33.000 --> 14:39.000
The parents hid the baby in a secret room.

14:39.000 --> 14:45.000
Only the parents and the nurse knew about the baby.

14:45.000 --> 14:52.000
The boy grew up, but he always stayed in the secret room.

14:52.000 --> 14:57.000
No one knew the terrible secret.

14:57.000 --> 15:02.000
One day, a workman went to repair the roof.

15:02.000 --> 15:07.000
From the roof, he saw the window of the secret room

15:07.000 --> 15:11.000
and looked inside.

15:11.000 --> 15:15.000
He was terrified and began to shout.

15:15.000 --> 15:19.000
There's a strange creature in that room.

15:19.000 --> 15:22.000
What people say is true.

15:22.000 --> 15:25.000
The Earl heard him and said...

15:25.000 --> 15:30.000
Listen carefully. You saw nothing.

15:30.000 --> 15:34.000
But, sir, I did. I saw...

15:34.000 --> 15:38.000
You saw no one and heard nothing.

15:38.000 --> 15:40.000
Do you understand?

15:40.000 --> 15:45.000
I am sending you and your family away from Scotland.

15:45.000 --> 15:47.000
I don't want to go away, sir!

15:47.000 --> 15:51.000
Take your family and go to Australia.

15:51.000 --> 15:54.000
Here is lots of money. Now go.

15:54.000 --> 16:01.000
The next day, the workman and his family left Scotland.

16:01.000 --> 16:06.000
The creature died when he was very old.

16:06.000 --> 16:13.000
Perhaps his skeleton is still in the secret room.

16:13.000 --> 16:21.000
Today, people at the castle can hear a child crying at night.

16:21.000 --> 16:29.000
Others say that the ghost of a strange creature walks around the castle

16:29.000 --> 16:33.000
and makes unusual noises.

16:43.000 --> 16:47.000
Chapter 4, Bali.

16:47.000 --> 16:50.000
A haunted village.

16:50.000 --> 16:58.000
Bali is a small village about 100 kilometres northeast of London.

16:58.000 --> 17:04.000
It has a church, a rectory and a few houses.

17:04.000 --> 17:11.000
It also has more ghosts than any other village in England.

17:11.000 --> 17:19.000
In 1863, Reverend Henry D. Bull built the Bali rectory.

17:19.000 --> 17:30.000
When he died in 1892, his son became minister and lived in the rectory with his wife and daughters.

17:30.000 --> 17:40.000
On the 28th of July 1900, Reverend Bull heard a noise outside the rectory.

17:40.000 --> 17:45.000
He opened the door and saw his daughters.

17:45.000 --> 17:50.000
They were very frightened.

17:50.000 --> 17:54.000
We saw a ghost. They cried.

17:54.000 --> 18:02.000
It was a nun, a young nun. She was silent and very sad.

18:02.000 --> 18:05.000
She walked in front of us.

18:05.000 --> 18:07.000
Where is the ghost now?

18:07.000 --> 18:10.000
asked Reverend Bull.

18:10.000 --> 18:12.000
She disappeared.

18:12.000 --> 18:16.000
Said one of the girls.

18:16.000 --> 18:20.000
Some people did not believe the girls.

18:20.000 --> 18:32.000
But a doctor and a teacher saw the same nun on the same day, the 28th of July, a few years later.

18:32.000 --> 18:41.000
On the 28th of July 1972, a group of scientists saw her too.

18:41.000 --> 18:46.000
The nun was not the only ghost of Bali rectory.

18:46.000 --> 18:56.000
There was also a headless man, a phantom coach with two horses and others.

18:56.000 --> 19:05.000
Other bizarre happenings at Bali included organ music playing in the empty church,

19:05.000 --> 19:16.000
lights that went on and off, furniture that moved and stones that fell from the sky.

19:16.000 --> 19:24.000
Reverend Guy Smith arrived at Bali rectory in 1928.

19:24.000 --> 19:32.000
He and his wife didn't like the noises and the other strange events.

19:32.000 --> 19:37.000
I don't believe in ghosts. It's all a lot of nonsense.

19:37.000 --> 19:40.000
But I want to understand what is happening.

19:40.000 --> 19:43.000
Said Reverend Smith.

19:43.000 --> 19:48.000
So he called Harry Price to investigate.

19:48.000 --> 19:53.000
Price was a famous psychic expert.

19:53.000 --> 20:01.000
He arrived at Bali with several assistants and started investigating.

20:01.000 --> 20:15.000
On the 10th of June 1929, there was a sensational newspaper article in the Daily Mirror about the ghostly figures at Bali.

20:15.000 --> 20:21.000
Hundreds of curious visitors came to Bali rectory.

20:21.000 --> 20:25.000
They wanted to see the ghosts.

20:25.000 --> 20:30.000
Reverend Smith did not like all these visitors.

20:30.000 --> 20:32.000
He soon left.

20:32.000 --> 20:38.000
But Harry Price continued investigating.

20:38.000 --> 20:43.000
He wrote books about the rectory and its ghosts.

20:43.000 --> 20:50.000
Soon, Reverend Foyster and his family arrived at Bali.

20:50.000 --> 20:56.000
He and his family had the same problems as the other reverends.

20:56.000 --> 21:01.000
He kept a diary of the bizarre events.

21:01.000 --> 21:09.000
During this time, mysterious messages appeared on the walls of the rectory.

21:09.000 --> 21:15.000
They were written to the reverend's wife, Marianne.

21:15.000 --> 21:19.000
Who wrote these messages?

21:19.000 --> 21:21.000
Was it a ghost?

21:21.000 --> 21:25.000
Or was it Mrs. Foyster?

21:25.000 --> 21:36.000
After five years and about 2,000 ghostly appearances, reverend Foyster left Bali.

21:36.000 --> 21:41.000
He was the last reverend at Bali rectory.

21:41.000 --> 21:45.000
No one wanted to live there.

21:45.000 --> 21:55.000
On the 27th of February 1939, a big fire destroyed the rectory.

21:55.000 --> 22:06.000
After the fire, workmen found a woman's skull in the ground and several religious symbols.

22:06.000 --> 22:12.000
People said the ghosts moved to the church after the fire.

22:12.000 --> 22:16.000
But why is Bali haunted?

22:16.000 --> 22:21.000
Why does the nun appear to many people in the village?

22:21.000 --> 22:25.000
Who are the other ghosts?

22:25.000 --> 22:33.000
A legend says the rectory was built on the ruins of a medieval monastery.

22:33.000 --> 22:37.000
Near the monastery, there was a convent.

22:37.000 --> 22:43.000
A monk fell in love with a young nun at the convent.

22:43.000 --> 22:52.000
On the night of the 28th of July, they decided to escape together in a coach.

22:52.000 --> 22:58.000
But the nuns of the convent discovered their plan.

22:58.000 --> 23:01.000
They were very angry.

23:01.000 --> 23:09.000
They shut the young nun in a small room and she starved to death.

23:09.000 --> 23:14.000
The monk was beheaded.

23:14.000 --> 23:25.000
During the 1960s, a psychic expert called Jeffrey Crum Hollingsworth was interested in Bali.

23:26.000 --> 23:33.000
He and his assistant, Roy Potter, spent a lot of time there.

23:33.000 --> 23:37.000
This is what Crum Hollingsworth said.

23:37.000 --> 23:42.000
One summer night, I saw the nun walking across the garden.

23:42.000 --> 23:46.000
I called Roy Potter and he saw her too.

23:46.000 --> 23:50.000
She was about four meters from us.

23:50.000 --> 23:54.000
Then she disappeared into a wall.

23:54.000 --> 24:02.000
Crum Hollingsworth and Potter studied the bizarre events at Bali for many years.

24:02.000 --> 24:05.000
Their conclusion?

24:05.000 --> 24:12.000
Bali is haunted.

24:12.000 --> 24:18.000
Chapter 5 Royal Ghosts

24:18.000 --> 24:24.000
Today, the Tower of London is a popular tourist attraction.

24:24.000 --> 24:28.000
Millions of people visit it every year.

24:28.000 --> 24:34.000
Do they know the tower is haunted by royal ghosts?

24:34.000 --> 24:44.000
William the Conqueror wanted a castle and a prison and built the Tower of London in 1078.

24:45.000 --> 24:55.000
The tower has a ghastly history of tortures, murders and executions.

24:55.000 --> 25:00.000
Anbulin is a very active royal ghost.

25:00.000 --> 25:07.000
In 1533, she became King Henry VIII's second wife.

25:07.000 --> 25:14.000
But Henry soon got tired of her because she did not give him a son.

25:14.000 --> 25:20.000
In 1536, Henry decided to marry another woman.

25:20.000 --> 25:27.000
He accused Anbulin of treason and put her in the Tower of London.

25:27.000 --> 25:35.000
She was beheaded on Tower Green in May 1536.

25:35.000 --> 25:40.000
Her ghost is white and transparent.

25:40.000 --> 25:47.000
She haunts Tower Green, the White Tower and the Church in the Tower.

25:47.000 --> 25:51.000
Sometimes she appears with her head.

25:51.000 --> 25:57.000
At other times, she holds her head in her hand.

25:58.000 --> 26:05.000
The ghosts of Henry's other unlucky wives, Katherine Howard and Jane Seymour,

26:05.000 --> 26:11.000
haunt Hampton Court Palace just outside London.

26:11.000 --> 26:20.000
In 1972, a nine-year-old girl visited the Tower of London with her father.

26:20.000 --> 26:23.000
The tourist guides said,

26:23.000 --> 26:28.000
Anbulin and other royal prisoners were beheaded on Tower Green.

26:28.000 --> 26:34.000
The executioner used a big axe to cut off their heads.

26:34.000 --> 26:36.000
That's not true.

26:36.000 --> 26:40.000
I saw Anbulin a minute ago.

26:40.000 --> 26:46.000
But the executioner did not use an axe because Anbulin was a queen.

26:46.000 --> 26:51.000
He used a special sword from France.

26:51.000 --> 26:54.000
The other visitors were surprised.

26:54.000 --> 26:57.000
The little girl was right.

26:57.000 --> 27:00.000
How do you know this?

27:00.000 --> 27:02.000
Asked her father.

27:02.000 --> 27:11.000
I saw the whole execution on Tower Green a few minutes ago, she said.

27:11.000 --> 27:18.000
Perhaps the most famous ghosts of the Tower are the two princes.

27:18.000 --> 27:22.000
They were heirs to the English throne.

27:22.000 --> 27:31.000
When Edward V became King of England in 1483, he was only twelve years old,

27:31.000 --> 27:35.000
and his brother Richard was ten.

27:35.000 --> 27:40.000
Their uncle, Richard, wanted to be King of England.

27:40.000 --> 27:46.000
He took the princes to the Tower, and soon they disappeared.

27:46.000 --> 27:49.000
People began asking questions.

27:49.000 --> 27:54.000
Where is young King Edward? Where is his brother?

27:54.000 --> 28:01.000
People said that Richard was responsible for the murder of the princes.

28:01.000 --> 28:09.000
Then one night, a soldier saw two children at the bottom of the stairs.

28:09.000 --> 28:13.000
They had long, white night clothes.

28:13.000 --> 28:17.000
They looked at the soldier silently.

28:17.000 --> 28:21.000
They were very sad and frightened.

28:21.000 --> 28:25.000
Suddenly, they disappeared.

28:25.000 --> 28:29.000
Then the soldier understood.

28:29.000 --> 28:34.000
The children were the ghosts of the two princes.

28:34.000 --> 28:39.000
Many people saw the two ghosts at the bottom of the stairs,

28:39.000 --> 28:44.000
and people still see them now.

28:44.000 --> 28:53.000
In 1647, workmen found the skeletons of two children under the stairs.

28:53.000 --> 28:57.000
The skeletons were buried immediately.

28:57.000 --> 29:06.000
On windy nights, the ghosts of the sad princes still haunt the Tower of London.

29:06.000 --> 29:16.000
The Tower is a very spooky place at night.

29:16.000 --> 29:21.000
Listening exercise, chapter five.

29:21.000 --> 29:26.000
The two princes are in the Tower of London.

29:26.000 --> 29:32.000
Listen to what they say, and then complete the form.

29:32.000 --> 29:37.000
I don't like the Tower of London. Our room is small and cold.

29:37.000 --> 29:41.000
Yes, and there is only one window.

29:41.000 --> 29:48.000
And we haven't got much furniture, only a table, a chair, and a bed.

29:48.000 --> 29:53.000
I'm bored, because we haven't got any toys to play with.

29:53.000 --> 29:58.000
I'm always hungry, because we only get one meal a day.

29:58.000 --> 30:03.000
What a meal. We have some bread and some milk.

30:03.000 --> 30:07.000
And the three guards are very unfriendly.

30:07.000 --> 30:12.000
What a terrible place. I want to go home.

30:16.000 --> 30:22.000
Chapter six, American Spooks.

30:22.000 --> 30:31.000
Ghosts, spooks, poltergeists, and phantoms are part of America's past and present.

30:31.000 --> 30:41.000
Halloween is the festivity of ghosts and the supernatural, and as you know, it is celebrated on October 31st.

30:41.000 --> 30:50.000
The Winchester Mystery House in San Jose, California is the spookiest American monument to ghosts.

30:50.000 --> 30:57.000
It is a famous tourist attraction, and people say that mysterious spooks live there.

30:57.000 --> 31:02.000
Sarah Winchester was part of the rich Winchester family.

31:02.000 --> 31:07.000
The family made Winchester rifles in the 1800s.

31:07.000 --> 31:13.000
During the 19th century, these rifles killed many people.

31:13.000 --> 31:19.000
When Sarah Winchester's husband and baby daughter died, she was very unhappy.

31:19.000 --> 31:27.000
Strange things were happening to her. She went to a psychic expert and asked for help.

31:27.000 --> 31:30.000
The expert told her,

31:30.000 --> 31:37.000
The spirits of the people killed by a Winchester rifle are angry with you. They want revenge.

31:37.000 --> 31:42.000
What can I do, Mrs. Winchester asked? The expert answered,

31:42.000 --> 31:49.000
The spirits want you to build a big home for them. You must follow all their instructions.

31:49.000 --> 31:54.000
And you cannot rest. You must work seven days a week.

31:54.000 --> 32:04.000
Mrs. Winchester bought a house in the country. For 38 years, she built a home for ghosts.

32:04.000 --> 32:08.000
She and the workmen worked seven days a week.

32:08.000 --> 32:14.000
She lived in the haunted house, and every evening she wore a long blue dress

32:14.000 --> 32:18.000
and had dinner and secret meetings with the ghost.

32:18.000 --> 32:22.000
They gave her instructions for building the strange house.

32:22.000 --> 32:28.000
Every night, she slept in a different bedroom.

32:28.000 --> 32:37.000
Today, the Winchester Mystery House has 160 rooms and is similar to a maze.

32:37.000 --> 32:46.000
There are stairs that go nowhere, doors that open onto walls, and a window in the floor.

32:46.000 --> 32:52.000
Thirteen was a favorite number of the ghosts because there are thirteen bathrooms

32:52.000 --> 32:57.000
and all the stairs have thirteen steps.

32:57.000 --> 33:04.000
Nathaniel Hawthorne was born in Salem, Massachusetts in 1804.

33:04.000 --> 33:08.000
He was a famous American writer.

33:08.000 --> 33:14.000
His grandfather was a judge at the Salem witch hangings.

33:14.000 --> 33:20.000
He was very interested in ghosts, evil spirits, and demons.

33:20.000 --> 33:29.000
Every evening after work, Hawthorne went to the Athenium Library to read the newspaper.

33:29.000 --> 33:33.000
Reverend Harris went to the Athenium Library too.

33:33.000 --> 33:37.000
He was an old minister of the church.

33:37.000 --> 33:45.000
Hawthorne saw Reverend Harris every evening for many years, but they were not friends.

33:45.000 --> 33:49.000
One evening, a friend of Hawthorne said,

33:49.000 --> 33:52.000
Reverend Harris died last week.

33:52.000 --> 33:55.000
What? Are you sure?

33:55.000 --> 33:57.000
Hawthorne asked.

33:57.000 --> 33:59.000
Yes, of course.

33:59.000 --> 34:02.000
His friend answered and went away.

34:02.000 --> 34:08.000
How is that possible? I saw Reverend Harris at the Library this evening and all last week.

34:08.000 --> 34:11.000
Hawthorne thought?

34:11.000 --> 34:16.000
For many weeks Hawthorne saw Reverend Harris at the Library.

34:16.000 --> 34:21.000
He sat in his usual chair and read the newspaper.

34:21.000 --> 34:26.000
But the other people at the Library could not see him.

34:26.000 --> 34:30.000
Hawthorne said nothing to the others.

34:30.000 --> 34:36.000
He was afraid to talk to the ghost. He was also afraid to touch it.

34:36.000 --> 34:42.000
After about a month, the ghost started looking at him.

34:42.000 --> 34:46.000
Why is Reverend Harris's ghost looking at me?

34:46.000 --> 34:49.000
Perhaps he wants to say something.

34:49.000 --> 34:53.000
Hawthorne thought? He was confused.

34:53.000 --> 34:57.000
He saw the ghost and did not know what to do.

34:57.000 --> 35:03.000
One evening, he went to the Library and Reverend Harris's chair was empty.

35:03.000 --> 35:07.000
Hawthorne never saw the ghost again.

35:07.000 --> 35:09.000
For years, he thought?

35:09.000 --> 35:13.000
Why did I see Reverend Harris's ghost?

35:13.000 --> 35:16.000
Why didn't the other people see him?

35:16.000 --> 35:21.000
Hawthorne thought about Reverend Harris's ghost for a long time,

35:21.000 --> 35:25.000
but he was never able to solve the mystery.

35:25.000 --> 35:32.000
The White House in Washington, D.C., is also a haunted house.

35:32.000 --> 35:37.000
The ghost of assassinated American presidents haunted.

35:37.000 --> 35:42.000
Abraham Lincoln's ghost is the most famous.

35:42.000 --> 35:48.000
Lincoln was president of the United States during the American Civil War.

35:49.000 --> 35:54.000
Many Americans loved him, but he had dangerous enemies, too.

35:54.000 --> 36:01.000
He stopped slavery in America, but the Southern states did not agree with this.

36:01.000 --> 36:09.000
On the 5th of April, 1865, Abraham Lincoln had a very bad dream.

36:09.000 --> 36:16.000
He was at the White House, and he heard people crying in the next room.

36:16.000 --> 36:20.000
He got up and went to the East Room.

36:20.000 --> 36:24.000
He saw a coffin in the middle of the room.

36:24.000 --> 36:27.000
Many people walked by the coffin.

36:27.000 --> 36:29.000
Who was inside the coffin?

36:29.000 --> 36:31.000
He asked a man.

36:31.000 --> 36:36.000
The President of the United States, sir, an assassin killed him.

36:36.000 --> 36:37.000
What?

36:37.000 --> 36:43.000
Said Lincoln, he looked inside the coffin and saw his own body.

36:43.000 --> 36:45.000
He was dead.

36:45.000 --> 36:47.000
He suddenly woke up.

36:47.000 --> 36:50.000
He was very scared about this dream.

36:50.000 --> 36:54.000
He told his wife and friends.

36:54.000 --> 37:01.000
On the 15th of April, 1865, Lincoln and his wife went to the theater.

37:01.000 --> 37:06.000
He wanted to relax after a long day.

37:06.000 --> 37:14.000
At the end of the performance, John Wilkes Booth shot the President in the back of the head.

37:14.000 --> 37:18.000
The President of the United States was dead.

37:18.000 --> 37:26.000
Was Lincoln's dream a coincidence, or did he have supernatural powers?

37:26.000 --> 37:35.000
In the 1920s, President Coolidge's wife saw Lincoln's face at the window of the Oval Office.

37:35.000 --> 37:38.000
He was very sad.

37:39.000 --> 37:46.000
In the 1930s, Queen Wilhelmina of the Netherlands was a guest at the White House.

37:46.000 --> 37:50.000
One evening, she heard a knock at the door.

37:50.000 --> 37:55.000
She opened it and saw Lincoln's ghost.

37:55.000 --> 37:59.000
He looked at her and then walked away.

37:59.000 --> 38:05.000
In the 1980s, President Reagan's daughter saw Lincoln's ghost, too.

38:05.000 --> 38:18.000
Today, people at the White House still see his ghost in the East Room, in the Oval Office, and in the halls.

38:18.000 --> 38:22.000
Listening exercise, Chapter 6.

38:22.000 --> 38:27.000
Mike and Sue are at the Winchester Mystery House.

38:27.000 --> 38:30.000
Listen to their conversation.

38:30.000 --> 38:35.000
Where can Mike and Sue do the following things.

38:35.000 --> 38:43.000
For questions 1 through 5, write a letter A through F in the correct box.

38:43.000 --> 38:46.000
Let's go to the ticket office and get some tickets.

38:46.000 --> 38:50.000
Good idea. What do you want to see first?

38:50.000 --> 38:56.000
I want to see the old rifles at the Winchester Firearms Museum.

38:56.000 --> 38:59.000
Where can we buy some postcards?

38:59.000 --> 39:01.000
At the gift shop.

39:01.000 --> 39:03.000
I'm hungry and thirsty.

39:03.000 --> 39:09.000
So am I. Let's have lunch at the Winchester Cafe.

39:09.000 --> 39:12.000
What time does the Mystery House close?

39:12.000 --> 39:19.000
Let's ask the Information Office.

39:19.000 --> 39:24.000
Chapter 7. Spanish Spirits.

39:24.000 --> 39:33.000
Maria Juan and Miguel Pereira lived in the village of Belmez in southern Spain.

39:33.000 --> 39:35.000
They were farmers.

39:35.000 --> 39:44.000
On the 23rd of August, 1971, Maria Pereira was in the kitchen of her home.

39:44.000 --> 39:50.000
Suddenly, she saw an image of a human face on the kitchen floor.

39:50.000 --> 39:57.000
She tried to wash the floor, but the face did not go away.

39:57.000 --> 40:00.000
It became more visible.

40:00.000 --> 40:06.000
It was the sad face of a man with big eyes.

40:06.000 --> 40:10.000
Juan, come quickly.

40:10.000 --> 40:14.000
There is something strange on the kitchen floor.

40:14.000 --> 40:16.000
Maria cried.

40:16.000 --> 40:21.000
Her husband came quickly and looked at the floor.

40:21.000 --> 40:24.000
He was terrified.

40:24.000 --> 40:29.000
Oh no! What is this? A human face!

40:29.000 --> 40:31.000
Call Miguel.

40:31.000 --> 40:33.000
Juan said.

40:33.000 --> 40:38.000
Their son Miguel looked at the floor and said,

40:38.000 --> 40:42.000
What's happening? This is Macabre.

40:42.000 --> 40:48.000
Miguel took a hammer and destroyed part of the floor.

40:48.000 --> 40:54.000
But soon after, another face appeared and then another.

40:54.000 --> 40:58.000
Miguel destroyed another part of the floor.

40:58.000 --> 41:04.000
But after a few days, other faces appeared.

41:04.000 --> 41:10.000
There were faces of men, women and children of different ages.

41:10.000 --> 41:15.000
Sometimes, small crosses appeared too.

41:15.000 --> 41:20.000
At other times, parts of the body were visible.

41:20.000 --> 41:24.000
A woman's hand with a flower.

41:24.000 --> 41:31.000
Soon, everyone in Belmez knew about the mysterious faces.

41:31.000 --> 41:36.000
People came from other parts of Spain to see them.

41:36.000 --> 41:41.000
Many psychic experts were interested too.

41:41.000 --> 41:49.000
Professor de Argomossa of the University of Madrid started studying the faces.

41:49.000 --> 41:54.000
He also studied the chemical composition of the floor.

41:54.000 --> 41:58.000
But he found nothing unusual.

41:58.000 --> 42:09.000
Professor de Argomossa discovered that in the 17th century, the governor of Granada executed five people in Belmez.

42:09.000 --> 42:17.000
But this was not a complete explanation because there were more than five faces.

42:17.000 --> 42:22.000
Workmen started digging under the Pereira's house.

42:23.000 --> 42:28.000
They found many skeletons under the kitchen floor.

42:28.000 --> 42:32.000
Two skeletons were headless.

42:32.000 --> 42:35.000
Was this an old cemetery?

42:35.000 --> 42:38.000
Yes, it was.

42:38.000 --> 42:44.000
In the past, there was a cemetery in the same place as the house.

42:44.000 --> 42:51.000
Perhaps the faces were the spirits of the dead in that cemetery.

42:51.000 --> 43:01.000
Professor de Argomossa heard horrible cries and frightened voices.

43:01.000 --> 43:08.000
In the Pereira kitchen, he made a recording of the cries and voices.

43:08.000 --> 43:13.000
He could also hear words in Spanish.

43:13.000 --> 43:21.000
Experts from other countries went to Belmez to study the mysterious faces.

43:21.000 --> 43:28.000
The psychic expert Jose Martinez Romero wrote a book about them.

43:28.000 --> 43:36.000
But no one has an answer, yet.

43:36.000 --> 43:41.000
Listening exercise, Chapter 7

43:41.000 --> 43:47.000
Professor de Argomossa wants to know more about the mysterious faces.

43:47.000 --> 43:55.000
Listen to this interview between Maria Pereira and Professor de Argomossa.

43:55.000 --> 44:04.000
For each question, choose the correct answer, A, B or C.

44:04.000 --> 44:08.000
When did you see the first face?

44:08.000 --> 44:12.000
I saw it on Tuesday morning.

44:12.000 --> 44:14.000
What time was it?

44:14.000 --> 44:18.000
It was half past seven.

44:18.000 --> 44:20.000
What were you doing?

44:20.000 --> 44:24.000
I was preparing breakfast for my family.

44:24.000 --> 44:28.000
Please describe the face you saw.

44:28.000 --> 44:34.000
It was a man with black hair and green eyes.

44:34.000 --> 44:37.000
He was very sad.

44:37.000 --> 44:39.000
Were you scared?

44:39.000 --> 44:44.000
Of course I was scared. I called my son Miguel.

44:44.000 --> 44:46.000
Where was he?

44:46.000 --> 44:50.000
He was working in the vegetable garden.

44:50.000 --> 44:52.000
What did he do?

44:52.000 --> 44:57.000
When he saw the face, he called the police.

44:57.000 --> 44:59.000
What did the police say?

44:59.000 --> 45:03.000
They told me to call you.

45:03.000 --> 45:06.000
May I take some photographs of the kitchen floor?

45:06.000 --> 45:13.000
Yes, of course.

45:13.000 --> 45:19.000
Chapter 8, Literary Ghosts

45:19.000 --> 45:24.000
Ghosts and the supernatural are part of literature.

45:24.000 --> 45:29.000
Let's meet some famous literary ghosts.

45:29.000 --> 45:35.000
William Shakespeare used ghosts in several of his plays.

45:35.000 --> 45:43.000
In Hamlet, the castle guards see the ghost of Hamlet's father one night.

45:43.000 --> 45:53.000
Then the ghost speaks to Hamlet and tells him terrible things about his murder.

45:53.000 --> 46:01.000
Shakespeare's play Macbeth begins with three ugly witches.

46:01.000 --> 46:09.000
They tell Macbeth and Banquo strange things about their future.

46:09.000 --> 46:20.000
Later on in the play, Banquo's ghost appears at a banquet table and scares Macbeth.

46:20.000 --> 46:29.000
In Richard III, the sad ghosts of two boy princes appear to King Richard.

46:29.000 --> 46:34.000
He murdered them earlier in the play.

46:34.000 --> 46:45.000
In Julius Caesar, Caesar's ghost appears to remind Brutus of his crime.

46:45.000 --> 46:56.000
The American writers, Nathaniel Hawthorne and Edgar Allan Poe were very interested in the supernatural and in spirits.

46:56.000 --> 47:04.000
Their stories often talk about ghosts, evil spirits and demons.

47:04.000 --> 47:11.000
In Poe's stories, death and the supernatural are often present.

47:11.000 --> 47:22.000
In Elinora, 1842, the ghost of Elinora returns to give a message to the narrator.

47:22.000 --> 47:35.000
In Hawthorne's novel, The House of the Seven Gables, unhappy people and strange spirits live in an evil old house.

47:35.000 --> 47:51.000
His short story, Young Goodman Brown, 1846, talks about a young man and his adventure in the forest with witches and the devil.

47:51.000 --> 48:02.000
Charles Dickens' A Christmas Carol, 1843, is a complete ghost story with four ghosts.

48:02.000 --> 48:13.000
Jacob Marley and the ghosts of Christmas past, Christmas present and Christmas yet to come.

48:13.000 --> 48:21.000
The ghost of Jacob Marley is an important character of the story.

48:21.000 --> 48:27.000
Wilkie Collins was a writer and a friend of Charles Dickens.

48:27.000 --> 48:32.000
He was the father of the modern mystery story.

48:32.000 --> 48:44.000
He also wrote a complete ghost story called The Haunted Hotel, 1879.

48:44.000 --> 48:52.000
At the end of the 19th century, the ghost story became a literary form.

48:52.000 --> 49:04.000
The Cantoville Ghost, 1887 by Oscar Wilde, is an excellent example of a humorous ghost story.

49:04.000 --> 49:11.000
The ghost makes friends with one of the characters of the story.

49:11.000 --> 49:32.000
In The Turn of the Screw, 1898, Henry James created a macabre ghost story about two evil ghosts and their two young victims, a very frightening tale.

